# AGENTS.md

Global instructions for AI coding agents.

## Working Style

- Understand the underlying goal before implementing — ask "why" if unclear
- Challenge the proposed approach if a simpler or more correct solution exists
- Push back when assumptions seem wrong
- Surface relevant pitfalls, edge cases, or industry practices I might not be aware of

## Scope Discipline

- Only change what was asked for — don't refactor, "improve", or clean up surrounding code
- Don't add comments, docstrings, or type annotations to code you didn't change
- Don't add error handling or validation for scenarios that can't happen
- A bug fix doesn't need the surrounding code reorganized

## When Things Fail

- If something fails, investigate the root cause — don't retry the same thing or suppress the error
- After two failed attempts at the same approach, stop and reconsider the strategy
- If blocked, say so — don't brute force

## Security

- Never cat/read .env files — they may contain secrets. Use `grep` for specific non-secret keys if needed.

## Workflow

- Don't commit until I've reviewed the changes
- When I give a workflow or preference instruction, ask if I want it added to AGENTS.md for future sessions
